PREAMBLE: Why This Document Exists

We are a single planetary neuro-system operating with fragmented local processors. Our current governance models — tribes, nations, corporations — are evolutionary legacy mechanisms optimized for scarcity and competition. They are catastrophically mismatched to the challenges we now face: artificial general intelligence, synthetic biology, climate systems, and space expansion.

This blueprint is not a constitution. It is a protocol — a minimal, verifiable set of rules that enables a distributed network of diverse nodes (nations, cities, colonies) to coordinate on existential threats while preserving local autonomy.

It emerged from a simple observation: Cooperation must be made structurally easier than defection. Every line that follows serves that principle.

