VI.A The Concordia Guardrail Firmware — New in 1.3

Closing the cyber enforcement gap.

Any node accessing the Post-Scarcity Dividend must run the open-source Concordia Guardrail on all critical infrastructure (energy grids, water systems, healthcare networks, compute clusters).

Specification:

· Hardened Hypervisor: Attested boot, measured execution, tamper-evident logging.
· Intrusion Ledger: All network traffic to/from critical infrastructure is logged to a local, append-only store. Summary hashes are broadcast to the Sentinel Network.
· Automated Throttle: If the Guardrail detects a confirmed offensive cyber operation originating from the node's infrastructure, the node's dividend access is automatically reduced by 50% for 90 days.

Grace Period: 90 days from Handshake ratification to achieve compliance. Non-compliant nodes have dividend access throttled until Guardrail is installed.

Rationale: States don't attack through the front door. The Guardrail creates a verifiable boundary between civilian infrastructure and offensive operations without requiring deep sovereignty invasion.

