VII. The Refusal Region (Auto-Calibrated)

Automated protection against existential stupidity — with honest uncertainty encoding and skin in the game.

The Epistemic Framework

1. Continuous Monitoring:
The Sentinel Network tracks all nodes for actions with potential species-level impact.

2. Risk Assessment (The Bayesian Ensemble):
Each action is assigned a probability distribution of causing a terminal event, based on an ensemble of open-source models:

· Frequentist models (historical analogies)
· Bayesian models (prior distributions updated with evidence)
· Adversarial models (worst-case scenarios)
· Expert elicitation (structured Delphi protocols)

3. Auto-Calibrated Refusal Threshold — New in 1.3
The system triggers a Hard Fault when the lower bound of the 90% confidence interval for existential catastrophe probability exceeds a threshold that auto-calibrates quarterly based on the network's measured false-positive rate.

Formula:
\text{Threshold}_{t+1} = \text{Threshold}_t \times (1 + \alpha \times (\text{FPR}_t - \text{Target FPR})) 


Where Target FPR = 0.1% (1 in 1,000 interventions may be false), and α is a damping factor (0.3) to prevent oscillation.

Rationale: If the system is too trigger-happy, the threshold rises; if it's missing real risks, the threshold falls. Politics becomes measurement.

4. Refusal Appeal Market — New in 1.3
Any node may stake Prediction Tokens (backed by Tech-Tree credits) on the outcome of a flagged risk.

· If the flagged action proceeds and causes no catastrophe within a specified window: Stakers who predicted "false alarm" win tokens from those who predicted "real risk."
· If a catastrophe occurs: Winners are those who predicted risk; losers' stakes flow to the Resilience Fund.
· Allocation: 70% to winning stakers, 30% to Resilience Fund.

Rationale: Turns epistemic disagreements into aligned incentives. Those most certain of safety put tokens behind their belief. Those most certain of danger are rewarded if they're right.

Multi-Modal Verification (The Oracle Shield)

No Hard Fault shall be triggered by a single data stream.
Requirement: Existential risk detection requires 3-of-5 Independent Modalities.

The Hard Fault Protocol

· Immediate: The node's relevant infrastructure is automatically throttled.
· Warning: A 24-hour pause for human review by a rotating panel of experts.
· Appeal: The node can present counter-evidence. Successful appeals log false positives and adjust calibration.

