VIII. The Civilizational Complexity Index (CCI)

A family of dashboards, not a single number. Now an open API.

Definition: The CCI is a suite of normalized composite indices (0–100) that track the health of the neuro-system from different stakeholder perspectives.

Core Components (Fixed)

Vector Component Proxy Metric
Energy (E) Abundance Global EROI + % clean energy
Knowledge (K) Access Open access publication rate + education equality
Cooperation (C) Integration Trade interdependence index + treaty compliance
Risk (R) Exposure Existential risk score (nuclear/bio/climate/AI)

Open API — New in 1.3

All underlying data is available via a public API. Any node may:

· Query raw time series
· Apply custom stakeholder weights
· Publish their own CCI variant
· Submit improved proxy metrics for consideration by the Kernel Council

Rationale: Prevents forking the protocol just to adjust weights. The data layer is universal; the interpretation layer is plural.

