IX. Adversarial Adoption Theory

Why adversarial nodes would join before their rivals.

The First-Mover Advantage Mechanism

1. Grandfathering Rights

· The first 10 nodes to ratify the Handshake receive permanent Kernel veto power on any expansion of the Relinquishments.

2. Genesis Fund Premium

· Early adopters (first 50 nodes) receive 3× voting weight in Genesis Fund allocation for the first 20 years.
· Micro-Handshake nodes receive the same premium for their first five years.

3. Tech-Tree Royalties

· Nodes that contribute foundational IP receive perpetual attribution and a small royalty stream (0.1%) from downstream commercial applications.

4. Security Backstop

· Early adopters receive priority insurance coverage — claims processed first in a global catastrophe.

5. Denial to Rivals

· Late joiners must accept rules set by early adopters. This transforms first-mover disadvantage into first-mover advantage.

