XI. Space Governance Protocol (Refined)

Extending the Handshake beyond Earth.

---

The Delta-V Economic Zone

Treat cis-lunar space as a distinct regulatory region with three sub-zones.

---

In-Situ Resource Utilization (ISRU) Mandate

· All off-world settlements must achieve material closure (>98% recycling) within 10 years.
· Priority on extracting water and metals from local sources.
· Failure to meet closure targets triggers automatic support withdrawal after 15 years.

---

The Sentinel Embassy — New in 1.3

Every off-world settlement with >100 permanent residents must host a permanent Sentinel Embassy:

· One human Sentinel (rotating assignment, trained in Refusal Protocol)
· One attested compute node with direct Earth uplink
· Local Refusal Region enforcement authority
· Earth kill-switch capability for existential-risk events

Rationale: 22-minute comms delay to Mars means a rogue hab could spin up a biolab before Earth sees telemetry. The Embassy closes that gap.

---

Governance Latency Protocol

· Earth-Moon: Real-time coordination possible.
· Earth-Mars: Autonomous authority granted; Earth retains veto on existential risks.
· All local laws logged to Sentinel Network within 24 hours.

---

Resource Rights: The Usufruct Principle

You do not own the territory; you own the right to use the resources, provided you contribute to the Civilizational Backup.

· Claim size: Proportional to demonstrated need and sustainable use plan.
· Duration: 50-year renewable leases.
· Transfer: Rights may be traded but not sold to non-compliant nodes.
· Backup contribution: 5% of extracted resources to Global Resilience Fund.

